records.addlTxt:
Amended Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading and enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of his/her client.   Amended Information charges Defendant as follows

AS TO COUNT 1:  MISDEMEANOR BATTERY, USE OF A DANGEROUS WEAPON, DOMESTIC ABUSE ASSESSMENTS, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 939.63(1)(a), 973.055(1) a Class A Misdemeanor. 

AS TO COUNT 2:  MISDEMEANOR BATTERY, USE OF A DANGEROUS WEAPON, DOMESTIC ABUSE ASSESSMENTS, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 939.63(1)(a), 973.055(1) a Class A Misdemeanor. 

AS TO COUNT 3:  MISDEMEANOR BATTERY, USE OF A DANGEROUS WEAPON, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 939.63(1)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor. 

AS TO COUNT 4:   DISORDERLY CONDUCT, USE OF A DANGEROUS WEAPON, DOMESTIC ABUSE ASSESSMENTS, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s)  947.01(1), 939.51(3)(b), 939.63(1)(a), 973.055(1) a Class B Misdemeanor.

Defendant Rachel Lee Ziegler appeared by video.  Attorney Andrew Joel Golden appeared by video for Rachel Lee Ziegler.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant ordered to serve 10 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent to counts 2 and 3, credit of 17 days days time served, Huber Privileges for work and childcare.  

AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant ordered to serve 10 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent to counts 1 and 3, credit of 17 days days time served, Huber Privileges for work and childcare.  

AS TO COUNT 3:  Defendant ordered to serve 10 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent to counts 1 and 2, credit of 17 days days time served, Huber Privileges for work and childcare.  

Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 24 MONTHS with the following conditions:

- No new laws rising to the level of probable cause.
- Comply with conditions of probation agent.
- Maintain absolute sobriety.  No illegal drugs.
- Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
- Mental health assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
- No use of possession of firearms.
- No contact with CW.  Probation agent may contact court to change no contact order and a future date.
- No violent contact with CZ and NW.
- Complete a batters intervention program.
- Court sets restitution at $0.
- Provide a DNA sample.
- AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2: Pay the DV surcharge on each count.
- Court advised defendant due to this DV conviction s/he may never possess firearms or ammunition. 
- Defendant to pay costs and surcharges (including DNA and DV) during period of probation.  If unpaid a civil judgment will be ordered filed against the defendant.

Court advised Defendant of her right to seek postconviction relief.

Defendant Rachel Lee Ziegler appeared by video.  Attorney Andrew Joel Golden appeared by video for Rachel Lee Ziegler.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO AMENDED COUNTS 1, 2, AND 3: Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank. 

AS TO AMENDED COUNT 4: Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders charge dismissed but read-in for sentencing purposes

Court advised defendant due to this DV conviction s/he may never possess firearms or ammunition.
